The paper discusses a widely used dimensionality reduction method for data visualization, which is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed model selection objective also involves analyzing similarities to Bayesian information criteria (BIC) and minimum description length (MDL), which are relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) and statistical learning (cs.SI).
